in the assembly -->
    <!-- add author's e-mail -->
    <meta name="maintainer" content="jsindelarova@suse.com" its:translate="no"/>
    <abstract><!-- can be changed via merge in the assembly -->
      <para>
       This section focuses on testing if the &ulpa; live patch works.
      </para>
    </abstract>
  </info>
  <para>
       After you prepare the live patch and its test program as described in <xref linkend="ulp-creating-patch"/>, you can test if the live patch works:
      </para>
      <procedure>
        <step>
          <para>
            Launch the test program:
          </para>
          <screen>&prompt.user;<command>LD_PRELOAD=/usr/lib64/libpulp.so.0 ./test</command></screen>
        </step>
        <step>
          <para>
            Install the live patch:
          </para>
          <screen>&prompt.user;<command>ulp trigger libc_livepatch.so</command></screen>
        </step>
      </procedure>
      <para>
        If the installation was successful, the &ulpa; tool displays the message <literal>SUCCESS</literal>. You should also see the <literal>glibc-livepatch</literal> message from the test program.
      </para>
</topic>
